    {
      "craigslist": {
        "url": "https://minneapolis.craigslist.org/hnp/apa/d/minneapolis-fully-furnished-apartment/7945014014.html",
        "posting_id": "7945014014",
        "title": "Fully Furnished Apartment Suite",
        "price": 1400,
        "price_text": "$1,400",
        "room": 1,
        "area": "",
        "loft": "1",
        "location": "",
        "full_address": "",
        "locality": "",
        "geocode_query": "",
        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post Monthly, weekly and daily rates available: Monthly: $1400 Weekly: $350 Daily: $65 + $45 cleaning fee. No damage deposit required. (Tenant will be responsible if damages are incurred.) I have other apartments available also. Please inquire for details. Contact Daniel at show contact info for information. (Unit 6) My 1895 era house is located in Uptown, one of the most walkable neighborhoods in Minneapolis. You’ll find yourself a short walk from the Walker Art Museum and its famous “Spoon Bridge” sculpture, Lake of the Isles, The Wedge Coop Grocery Store, Spyhouse Coffee and The Basilica of St. Mary. I will provide you with a key upon arrival. You are renting one of six units in my home. I am available as you need me to be. Don't hesitate to call or text with questions, even if you just need a restaurant suggestion. I'm here! My name is Daniel. I purchased this house in 2001 and have been lovingly renovating it ever since. I have honored the spirit of the original building while thoughtfully adding my own touches and inspiration. One of my great passions in life is Argentine Tango, so I named each apartment after a beloved Argentine musician. If you are curious about the dance scene in the Twin Cities, I’m happy to point you towards the best milongas and I also offer lessons. Other things to note If I were visiting Minneapolis and could only do one thing, I'd rent a Nice Ride and bike around the sparkling chain of Lakes. Lake of the Isles, Lake Bde Maka Ska and Lake Harriet are all nearby. Pop over to Spyhouse Coffee for a caffeine fix or stop at Nightingale for oysters and other fancy bar snacks. More time to enjoy? Stroll over to the Walker Art Center and take a selfie in the outdoor sculpture garden with the iconic \"Spoon Bridge\" or cherry on a spoon. Or head over to Eat Street on Nicollet Ave for a whole world of dining options and pay a visit to the Minneapolis Art Institute. Other popular stops in the Twin Cities are The Guthrie Theater, Stone Arch Bridge, Surly Brewing Co for craft beers and delicious food, or a visit to the iconic Mall of America. We’ve got plenty to offer sports fans too with the Minnesota Twins at Target Field, the Timberwolves at Target Center and the Vikings at U.S Bank Stadium.",
