        "mainpic": "a2be0d7d-9cf8-4ca8-9192-ab9724dd485b",
        "msg": "QR Code Link to This Post Contact Daniel at show contact info . \"Tango Footstop\" Furnished Suite Apartment Uptown Monthly rate - $1725 WEEKLY rate - $450 Daily rate - $75 + $60 cleaning fee No damage deposit required. (Tenant will be responsible if damages are incurred.) (I also have other apartments available. Please inquire for details) Enjoy modern amenities and convenience in a house where the romance and splendor of the Victorian era have been lovingly preserved. This suite features a brand new queen size bed with 500 thread count linens. In the kitchen, an automatic Keurig coffee and tea maker along with pods starts your morning with ease and style. A fully equipped kitchen featuring beautiful granite countertops makes eating in fun. Meal prep is simple with a full set of cookware, knives and spices. Enjoy your meal on bone china with linen napkins. You’ll find it well stocked with shampoo, conditioner, body wash, a fresh bar of soap and fluffy white towels. Guests also have access to the washer and dryer and free off-street parking. My 1895 era house is located in Uptown, one of the most walkable neighborhoods in Minneapolis. You’ll find yourself a short walk from the Walker Art Museum and its famous “Spoon Bridge” sculpture, Lake of the Isles, The Wedge Coop Grocery Store, Spyhouse Coffee and The Basilica of St. Mary. Guest access I will provide you with a key upon arrival. You are renting one of six units in my home. I am as available as you need me to be. Don't hesitate to call or text with questions, even if you just need a restaurant suggestion. I'm here! My name is Daniel. I purchased this house in 2001 and have been lovingly renovating it ever since. I have honored the spirit of the original building while thoughtfully adding my own touches and inspiration. One of my great passions in life is Argentine Tango so I named each apartment after a beloved Argentine musician. If you are curious about the dance scene in the Twin Cities, I’m happy to point you towards the best milongas and I also offer lessons.",
