        "description": "QR Code Link to This Post 1515 Chicago Ave, Minneapolis, MN 55404 NOW AVAILABLE! Buri Manor offers 38 efficiency apartment homes. A community garden and landscaped courtyard provides a small oasis in the midst of an urban setting. Development History Built in 1986, Buri Manor was Aeon's first housing development. The development was built to help replace the 350 units that were destroyed when the Minneapolis Convention Center was created. With funding from the Family Housing Fund, Aeon partnered with Elliot Park Neighborhood, Inc. and Brighton Development Corporation to remove a detrimental neighborhood bar to preserve necessary homes. Buri Manor, named in honor of community activist Isabel Buri, was honored with the Design Award from the Minneapolis Committee on Urban Environment (CUE) in 1987. Amenities Include: BBQ/Picnic Area On-Site Parking Computer Lab Handicap Accessible Community Room On-Site Maintenance On-Site Laundry Landscaped Courtyard On-Site Management Smoke-Free On Bus Line Night Patrol Call: show contact info For more information, visit us at: https://liveaeon.org/n6rpfz7h/buri-manor",
